import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='Date', y='CO2', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['CO2'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean CO2 concentration')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('CO2 concentration (ppm)')
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="darkgrid")
    sns.histplot(data=data, x="CO2", kde=True, color="blue")
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean = {data['CO2'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].median(), color='g', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median = {data['CO2'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Date', y='CO2', data=data, ax=ax, label='Unadjusted CO2')
    sns.lineplot(x='Date', y='adjusted_CO2', data=data, ax=ax, label='Adjusted CO2')
    plt.title('How does the adjusted CO2 concentration compare to the unadjusted CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('CO2 Concentration (ppm)')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.groupby(data['Year'].dt.year)['CO2'].mean().reset_index()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='Year', y='CO2', data=data, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['CO2'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average CO2 concentration')
    ax.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Average CO2 concentration (ppm)')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    plt.title('What is the average CO2 concentration per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
